==Russian==

===Noun===
'''гопник''' (gópnik), ''plural:'' '''гопники''' (gópniki) 

# a member of Russian urban criminal subculture '''[[гопники]]'''; a young [[hoodlum]], a member of a street [[gang]].
# a young [[bully]] or any [[rowdy]] youth.
# an aggressive, poorly educated and [[ill-mannered]] person, even if not too young. 

